#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/uvcvideo.rst:116
msgid ""
"This ioctl creates a mapping between a UVC control or part of a UVC control "
"and a V4L2 control. Once mappings are defined, userspace applications can "
"access vendor-defined UVC control through the V4L2 control API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/uvcvideo.rst:121
msgid ""
"To create a mapping, applications fill the uvc_xu_control_mapping structure "
"with information about an existing UVC control defined with UVCIOC_CTRL_ADD "
"and a new V4L2 control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/uvcvideo.rst:125
msgid ""
"A UVC control can be mapped to several V4L2 controls. For instance, a UVC "
"pan/tilt control could be mapped to separate pan and tilt V4L2 controls. The "
"UVC control is divided into non overlapping fields using the 'size' and "
"'offset' fields and are then independently mapped to V4L2 control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/drivers/uvcvideo.rst:131
msgid ""
"For signed integer V4L2 controls the data_type field should be set to "
"UVC_CTRL_DATA_TYPE_SIGNED. Other values are currently ignored."
